00:13:34.190 --> 00:13:37.660
make an mRNA that the proteins
are going to be getting

00:13:37.660 --> 00:13:38.752
fired off at some rate.

00:13:38.752 --> 00:13:40.460
But eventually it's
going to be degraded.

00:13:40.460 --> 00:13:42.305
It's a competition
between those two rates

00:13:42.305 --> 00:13:45.340
that determines basically
how many proteins,

00:13:45.340 --> 00:13:48.219
how many times do you fire
off a protein before you

00:13:48.219 --> 00:13:48.760
get degraded.

00:13:52.930 --> 00:13:54.230
